      "writtenOn": "2021-07-14T12:25:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My gut says that for the porter-duff blend modes, we could add a tolerance and get away with that. (Even for those, I expect the precision of the shader-based vs. fixed-function blending to be different). Once we get to the wackier modes, things are pretty inconsistent among devices. Still, a unit test for all of the common ones would be nice. (We have some other unit tests that check things with a tolerance - and some of those even use a larger tolerance on low-end GPUs where the shader precision is bad).",
